      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "Minimum wage hikes are a complex issue, but for small businesses in lower cost-of-living areas, they often lead to increased operational costs. These businesses frequently absorb the higher labor expenses by either raising prices or cutting back on non-essential services. While proponents argue it helps workers, the reality for small, local enterprises is often a squeeze on already tight margins.",
