      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "The push for mandates often comes from urban centers with different economic realities, and their solutions don't fit rural life. A better approach is to focus on tax incentives and deregulation for small businesses, allowing them to manage their costs without government interference. Local economies thrive when businesses have the flexibility to adapt to their specific community needs, not when they are forced into a one-size-fits-all policy.",
      "source": "target",
